\n<div>\n Atlas Hotel</div>\n<div>\n<a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-qQmTuAdlgJk/UV00KmyOL4I/AAAAAAAAI0Y/3q2dxB3KyrM/s1600/Gloria+hotel.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="320" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-qQmTuAdlgJk/UV00KmyOL4I/AAAAAAAAI0Y/3q2dxB3KyrM/s320/Gloria+hotel.jpg" width="240"></a></div>\n<div>\n Gloria Hotel</div>\n<div>\n<a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-gYVvsn1GMs0/UV00Ns4FgyI/AAAAAAAAI0g/uEAcph18B50/s1600/Excelsior+Hotel.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="320" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-gYVvsn1GMs0/UV00Ns4FgyI/AAAAAAAAI0g/uEAcph18B50/s320/Excelsior+Hotel.jpg" width="240"></a></div>\n<div>\nExcelsior Hotel </div>\n<div>\n<a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-RrrIvIhDhVY/UV00R3HWEWI/AAAAAAAAI0o/RsmuHJsbmOs/s1600/Hamra+Hotel.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="240" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-RrrIvIhDhVY/UV00R3HWEWI/AAAAAAAAI0o/RsmuHJsbmOs/s320/Hamra+Hotel.jpg" width="320"></a></div>\n<div>\n Hamra Hotel</div>\n<div>\n<a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-ybdkhNSQmwo/UV00Y5byERI/AAAAAAAAI0w/cTYbCFQWZQU/s1600/Napoli+Hotel.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="240" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-ybdkhNSQmwo/UV00Y5byERI/AAAAAAAAI0w/cTYbCFQWZQU/s320/Napoli+Hotel.jpg" width="320"></a></div>\n<div>\n Napoli Hotel</div>\n<div>\n<a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-4TYFwmRhi0U/UV00ax33LzI/AAAAAAAAI04/ZOV7qcHq490/s1600/Palm+Beach+hotel.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="240" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-4TYFwmRhi0U/UV00ax33LzI/AAAAAAAAI04/ZOV7qcHq490/s320/Palm+Beach+hotel.jpg" width="320"></a></div>\n<div>\nPalm Beach hotel </div>\n<div>\n<a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-tIYunjt5pTk/UV00hmhYk3I/AAAAAAAAI1A/6aHz4eSl28U/s1600/Semiramis+hotel.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="240" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-tIYunjt5pTk/UV00hmhYk3I/AAAAAAAAI1A/6aHz4eSl28U/s320/Semiramis+hotel.jpg" width="320"></a></div>\n<div>\n Semiramis Hotel</div>\n<div>\n<a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-S1ZOTN-F8iw/UV00k1a6vVI/AAAAAAAAI1I/zjiMXCzWP9c/s1600/Paradise+Furnished+Appartments.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="320" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-S1ZOTN-F8iw/UV00k1a6vVI/AAAAAAAAI1I/zjiMXCzWP9c/s320/Paradise+Furnished+Appartments.jpg" width="240"></a></div>\n<div>\nParadise furnished apartments</div>\n<br>\nBeirut/NTSC is proud to bring you a new series "... But you can never leave", based on the old hotels of Beirut which have ceased to exist mainly, I am revisiting places of the memory, to investigate and to anchor. And remember, as the Eagles once told us "you can check out any time you like... but you can never leave." Enjoy!</div>'),
(941, 'http://ginosblog.com/2013/04/04/gnr-bassist-tommy-stinson-falls-in-love-with-beirut-gets-rejected-by-radio-beirut/', 'GnR Bassist Tommy Stinson Falls in Love With Beirut, Gets Rejected by Radio Beirut', 'http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/image_1364979101180629.jpg?w=610&h=813', 'So, after all the fuss about Guns N Roses playing in Tel Aviv and what not, one member of the band, Tommy Stinson (no re...', 'ginosblog', 1365064260, '<p><a href="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/image_1364979101180629.jpg"><img alt="image_1364979101180629" src="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/image_1364979101180629.jpg?w=610&h=813" width="610" height="813"></a></p>\n<p>So, after all the fuss about Guns N Roses playing in Tel Aviv and what not, one member of the band, Tommy Stinson (no relation to Barney =P) decided to stay a few more days saying “I have a good feeling about Beirut, I wanted to stay and write some music and songs here.”</p>\n<p>Radio Beirut in Mar Mikhail is known for letting bands come and jam, no hassle, no drama, no door policy. The kind of place you’d find free spirits and would-be hippies and hipsters. In other words, a place I’d go to if I’m not in the mood for the usual Lebanese drama and elaborate rituals of getting into a pub or club. I was there last Thursday as a matter of fact and got a grip of what the place is all about.</p>\n<p>Tommy wanted to go there, and when the management checked with Radio Beirut, they were met with:</p>\n<blockquote><p>RB: So, X told me Axl rose wants to come sing?<br>\nJK: No, axl doesnt come that much, tommy wants to come sing his own stuff.<br>\nRB: Oh. Tell him we’re sorry we don’t accept him here, on behalf of all radio beirut staff, cause he played in Tel Aviv and he played their anthem.<br>\nJK: Ok, but they also played our anthem. And it’s music.<br>\nRB: Make sure he gets my message, it’s important.<br>\nJK: I won’t, cause i don’t support it.</p>\n<p><em>This was reported to me by a friend close to the promoters.</em></p></blockquote>\n<p>The funny part is that when the RB manager thought it was Axl, and looked receptive (according to the conversation relayed to me by my friend), but when he found out it’s just the bassist, it’s as if he suddenly remembered his fervent support of the boycott and divestment of Israel.</p>\n<p>Anyway, the good news is that Tommy, who fell in love with Beirut and plans to come, did get to play his own original songs live for the audience at Rules. He was even joined by Nader, from The Wanton Bishops, who after Saturday, were a <em>massive </em>hit amongst Lebanese rock lovers (or at least the ones I got to talk to =P).</p>\n<p>I’m glad that the band didn’t know of what happened and that they, or one of them at least, had the chance to experience the charm of Beirut away from politics and rigid ideologies. I’m also proud he felt so inspired that he stayed with a friend for 4 extra days to write up some new material. I hope one day we’ll stop tarnishing the arts and culture world with our shortsighted dogmatic politics, and just let the people enjoy themselves and the artists showcase their work. Till then though, let’s hope the reasonable people who just want to enjoy the music can still operate under the pressure and emotional blackmail that refuses to go away.</p>\n<p>Here’s the YouTube video:</p>\n<p><span><iframe type="text/html" width="610" height="374" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/4F9XJ2wwbiU?version=3&rel=1&fs=1&showsearch=0&showinfo=1&iv_load_policy=1&wmode=transparent" frameborder="0"></iframe></span></p>\n\n<a href="http://ginosblog.com/2013/04/04/gnr-bassist-tommy-stinson-falls-in-love-with-beirut-gets-rejected-by-radio-beirut/image_1364979020121232/" title="image_1364979020121232"><img data-liked="0" data-reblogged="0" data-attachment-id="12872" data-orig-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/image_1364979020121232.jpg" data-orig-size="720,960" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta=''{"aperture":"0","credit":"","camera":"","caption":"","created_timestamp":"0","copyright":"","focal_length":"0","iso":"0","shutter_speed":"0","title":""}'' data-image-title="image_1364979020121232" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/image_1364979020121232.jpg?w=225" data-large-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/image_1364979020121232.jpg?w=610" width="112" height="150" src="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/image_1364979020121232.jpg?w=112&h=150" alt="image_1364979020121232"></a>\n<a href="http://ginosblog.com/2013/04/04/gnr-bassist-tommy-stinson-falls-in-love-with-beirut-gets-rejected-by-radio-beirut/image_1364979183744961/" title="image_1364979183744961"><img data-liked="0" data-reblogged="0" data-attachment-id="12871" data-orig-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/image_1364979183744961.jpg" data-orig-size="720,960" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta=''{"aperture":"0","credit":"","camera":"","caption":"","created_timestamp":"0","copyright":"","focal_length":"0","iso":"0","shutter_speed":"0","title":""}'' data-image-title="image_1364979183744961" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/image_1364979183744961.jpg?w=225" data-large-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/image_1364979183744961.jpg?w=610" width="112" height="150" src="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/image_1364979183744961.jpg?w=112&h=150" alt="image_1364979183744961"></a>\n<a href="http://ginosblog.com/2013/04/04/gnr-bassist-tommy-stinson-falls-in-love-with-beirut-gets-rejected-by-radio-beirut/image_1364979101180629/" title="image_1364979101180629"><img data-liked="0" data-reblogged="0" data-attachment-id="12870" data-orig-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/image_1364979101180629.jpg" data-orig-size="720,960" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta=''{"aperture":"0","credit":"","camera":"","caption":"","created_t