(1051, 'http://www.nogarlicnoonions.com/empire-premiere-cinema-lazyboy-and-premium-sushi/', 'Empire Premiere: Cinema, Lazyboy and Premium Sushi', NULL, 'I recently had the chance to get a sneak preview of the menu and too be honest I was super impressed that I just had to ...', 'nogarlicnoonions', 1365400800, 'I recently had the chance to get a sneak preview of the menu and too be honest I was super impressed that I just had to go back there for another peek of the new luxury way of watching a movie. Empire Premiere Sodeco is an experience from the moment you enter the venue until<a href="http://www.nogarlicnoonions.com/empire-premiere-cinema-lazyboy-and-premium-sushi/">  »more...</a>'),
(1052, 'http://inkontheside.com/2013/04/08/flirting/', 'Flirting', 'http://inkontheside.com/comics-rss/2013-04-08-Flirting.jpg', 'There’s a time and place for everything fellas, a time and place for everything.. Have a great week!', 'inkontheside', 1365401880, '<p><a href="http://inkontheside.com/2013/04/08/flirting/" title="Flirting"><img src="http://inkontheside.com/comics-rss/2013-04-08-Flirting.jpg" alt="Flirting" title="Flirting"></a></p>There’s a time and place for everything fellas, a time and place for everything.. Have a great week!'),
(1053, 'http://beirutspring.com/blog/2013/04/08/jumblats-irish-peace/', 'Jumblat’s Irish Peace', 'http://beirutspring.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/belfast-fish.jpg', 'Something is cooking in Mukhtara\n– Could this be where Lebanon’s future is built? –\nThe sage of the mountains may ...', 'beirutspring', 1365406440, '<p><strong>Something is cooking in Mukhtara</strong></p>\n<p><img src="http://beirutspring.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/belfast-fish.jpg"><br><span>– Could this be where Lebanon’s future is built? –</span></p>\n<p>The sage of the mountains may have his quirks, but one of his redeeming qualities is his ability to gaze into the future and start planning. His next plan: Disarming Hezbollah amicably using a long term peace process inspired by the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northern_Ireland_peace_process">Good Friday Agreement</a> that helped bring peace to Northern Ireland.</p>\n<p>In his recent <em>Kalam el Nass</em> interview, Mr. Jumblat focused many times on “oranizing our internal affairs”, and he kept mentioning the irish peace process as a good model. For those who don’t know, the Belfast Agreement came out of a process that took a long time, most of which was spent on building trust and imagining a mutually beneficial future for the northern Irish people.</p>\n<p>The British Ambassador in Beirut, no doubt happy with the prospect that his country may play a role in bringing lasting peace to Lebanon, jumped at the opportunity and tweeted <a href="https://twitter.com/HMATomFletcher/status/321129261362724864">this</a> this moring: </p>\n<blockquote width="500"><p>Pleased that Walid Joumblatt has accepted invitations to visit Belfast& London next week. Discussions to focus on reconciliation&stability.</p>\n<p>— Tom Fletcher (@HMATomFletcher) <a href="https://twitter.com/HMATomFletcher/status/321129261362724864">April 8, 2013</a></p></blockquote>\n<p><script async src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p>\n<p>The symbolic overtones of this trip should no be missed on anyone.</p>\n<h2>In search of a long term plan</h2>\n<p>Mr. Jumblat’s movement on this issue is based on two assumptions:</p>\n<ul><li>The Syrian regime is finished</li>\n<li>The Taef Agreement is showing its age</li>\n</ul><p>Mr. Jumblat realizes that Hezbollah now has to make a strategic choice after the demise of the Syrian regime: Push with further militarization and isolation, or fully integrate with the Lebanese state. He calculates that what might tip the scales towards the second option is more political and economic empowerment for Lebanon’s Shiaas.</p>\n<p>Walid Jumblat’s message seems to be: Now is the best time to make an historic agreement with Lebanon’s Shiaas. It will take time, effort and concessions from all sides, but the payoff could be a peaceful, sovereign country with one government and one Army.</p>\n<hr><h2><span>✒ Is <em>Beirut Spring</em> Lebanon’s Best News blog?</span></h2>\n<p><a href="http://smabeirut.com/"><img src="http://beirutspring.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/81x300-bw-sma-bs-logos.png"></a></p>\n<p>I was happy to learn that <em>Beirut spring</em> was selected as a finalist in the <strong><a href="http://smabeirut.com/?category=1">“blog of the year”</a></strong> and <strong><a href="http://smabeirut.com/?category=2">“best news blog”</a></strong> categories in Beirut’s <em>Social Media Awards</em>. </p>\n<p>If you believe that this blog deserves to be recognized as such, kindly vote for it at <a href="http://smabeirut.com/">www.smabeirut.com</a>. It will take two seconds and you’ll have my eternal grattitude.. </p>\n<div>\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/beirutspring/fb_feed?a=dIC6UBbE4A0:W40RwAMNTOw:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/beirutspring/fb_feed?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/beirutspring/fb_feed?a=dIC6UBbE4A0:W40RwAMNTOw:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/beirutspring/fb_feed?i=dIC6UBbE4A0:W40RwAMNTOw:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/beirutspring/fb_feed?a=dIC6UBbE4A0:W40RwAMNTOw:F7zBnMyn0Lo"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/beirutspring/fb_feed?i=dIC6UBbE4A0:W40RwAMNTOw:F7zBnMyn0Lo" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/beirutspring/fb_feed?a=dIC6UBbE4A0:W40RwAMNTOw:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/beirutspring/fb_feed?i=dIC6UBbE4A0:W40RwAMNTOw:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/beirutspring/fb_feed?a=dIC6UBbE4A0:W40RwAMNTOw:qj6IDK7rITs"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/beirutspring/fb_feed?d=qj6IDK7rITs" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/beirutspring/fb_feed?a=dIC6UBbE4A0:W40RwAMNTOw:J3aVl1i_38o"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/beirutspring/fb_feed?d=J3aVl1i_38o" border="0"></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/beirutspring/fb_feed/~4/dIC6UBbE4A0" height="1" width="1">'),
