(1106, 'http://ginosblog.com/2013/04/09/uber-lyft-and-zimride-cheap-and-fun-ways-to-get-around-in-the-us/', 'Uber, Lyft and Zimride: Cheap and Fun Ways to Get Around in the US', NULL, 'We see a lot of promising startups springing up everywhere. It’s rare to see one actually take off and become a part o...', 'ginosblog', 1365523980, '<p>We see a lot of promising startups springing up everywhere. It’s rare to see one actually take off and become a part of our daily days though. Speaking of successful startups, I love going to San Francisco because <em>everything</em> cool and techie gets tested out there first. It’s just a stone’s throw away from most of the big tech and internet companies’ headquarters and the perfect urban setting to test out new apps and services and further develop them before launching them on a wider scale.</p>\n<p>Here are 3 apps/services I used in SF and LA over the weekend, maybe it’ll help you save time and money and make some friends if you ever visit, or, better yet, maybe you can develop something like that back home. Some are still new and limited, others are now all over the US and different parts of the world. I hope you find them as useful as I did!</p>\n<h2><a href="https://www.uber.com/">Uber</a></h2>\n<p>So, Uber is everywhere now. It’s in dozens of US cities and even places outside the US like London, Paris, Lyon Rome, Milan, Munich, Melbourne, Sydney, Toronto and Amsterdam. The idea is you sign up on your iOS or Android device and keep your credit card on file. If you need a taxi, all you do is tset your location and choose what type of car you want sent: plain-old taxi, an UberX car (hybrid, small usually), a black car (classier, spacier) or an SUV (for luggage and big groups I guess).</p>\n<p>I tried it in SF and here are the screenshots I took to sort of walk you through the super-simple process. All you do is hop on, sit, get off and once you’re off, it’ll be charged automatically on the app for you to verify and rate.</p>\n\n<a href="http://ginosblog.com/2013/04/09/uber-lyft-and-zimride-cheap-and-fun-ways-to-get-around-in-the-us/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-07-18/" title="Screenshot_2013-04-07-10-07-18"><img data-liked="0" data-reblogged="0" data-attachment-id="12943" data-orig-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-07-18.png" data-orig-size="720,1280" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta=''{"aperture":"0","credit":"","camera":"","caption":"","created_timestamp":"0","copyright":"","focal_length":"0","iso":"0","shutter_speed":"0","title":""}'' data-image-title="Screenshot_2013-04-07-10-07-18" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-07-18.png?w=168" data-large-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-07-18.png?w=576" width="84" height="150" src="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-07-18.png?w=84&h=150" alt="I set my location with the help of GPS and dragging and dropping"></a>\n<a href="http://ginosblog.com/2013/04/09/uber-lyft-and-zimride-cheap-and-fun-ways-to-get-around-in-the-us/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-08-11/" title="Screenshot_2013-04-07-10-08-11"><img data-liked="0" data-reblogged="0" data-attachment-id="12944" data-orig-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-08-11.png" data-orig-size="720,1280" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta=''{"aperture":"0","credit":"","camera":"","caption":"","created_timestamp":"0","copyright":"","focal_length":"0","iso":"0","shutter_speed":"0","title":""}'' data-image-title="Screenshot_2013-04-07-10-08-11" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-08-11.png?w=168" data-large-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-08-11.png?w=576" width="84" height="150" src="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-08-11.png?w=84&h=150" alt="Get an estimate for your ride"></a>\n<a href="http://ginosblog.com/2013/04/09/uber-lyft-and-zimride-cheap-and-fun-ways-to-get-around-in-the-us/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-08-36/" title="Screenshot_2013-04-07-10-08-36"><img data-liked="0" data-reblogged="0" data-attachment-id="12945" data-orig-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-08-36.png" data-orig-size="720,1280" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta=''{"aperture":"0","credit":"","camera":"","caption":"","created_timestamp":"0","copyright":"","focal_length":"0","iso":"0","shutter_speed":"0","title":""}'' data-image-title="Screenshot_2013-04-07-10-08-36" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-08-36.png?w=168" data-large-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-08-36.png?w=576" width="84" height="150" src="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-08-36.png?w=84&h=150" alt="Get notified that the car is there"></a>\n<a href="http://ginosblog.com/2013/04/09/uber-lyft-and-zimride-cheap-and-fun-ways-to-get-around-in-the-us/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-13-02/" title="Screenshot_2013-04-07-10-13-02"><img data-liked="0" data-reblogged="0" data-attachment-id="12946" data-orig-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-13-02.png" data-orig-size="720,1280" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta=''{"aperture":"0","credit":"","camera":"","caption":"","created_timestamp":"0","copyright":"","focal_length":"0","iso":"0","shutter_speed":"0","title":""}'' data-image-title="Screenshot_2013-04-07-10-13-02" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-13-02.png?w=168" data-large-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-13-02.png?w=576" width="84" height="150" src="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-13-02.png?w=84&h=150" alt="Follow your progress"></a>\n<a href="http://ginosblog.com/2013/04/09/uber-lyft-and-zimride-cheap-and-fun-ways-to-get-around-in-the-us/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-13-36/" title="Screenshot_2013-04-07-10-13-36"><img data-liked="0" data-reblogged="0" data-attachment-id="12947" data-orig-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-13-36.png" data-orig-size="720,1280" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta=''{"aperture":"0","credit":"","camera":"","caption":"","created_timestamp":"0","copyright":"","focal_length":"0","iso":"0","shutter_speed":"0","title":""}'' data-image-title="Screenshot_2013-04-07-10-13-36" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-13-36.png?w=168" data-large-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-13-36.png?w=576" width="84" height="150" src="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-13-36.png?w=84&h=150" alt="How cute is that tiny yellow car"></a>\n<a href="http://ginosblog.com/2013/04/09/uber-lyft-and-zimride-cheap-and-fun-ways-to-get-around-in-the-us/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-21-44/" title="Screenshot_2013-04-07-10-21-44"><img data-liked="0" data-reblogged="0" data-attachment-id="12948" data-orig-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-21-44.png" data-orig-size="720,1280" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta=''{"aperture":"0","credit":"","camera":"","caption":"","created_timestamp":"0","copyright":"","focal_length":"0","iso":"0","shutter_speed":"0","title":""}'' data-image-title="Screenshot_2013-04-07-10-21-44" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-21-44.png?w=168" data-large-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-21-44.png?w=576" width="84" height="150" src="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-07-10-21-44.png?w=84&h=150" alt="Get the bill, rate the driver and add a comment"></a>\n<a href="http://ginosblog.com/2013/04/09/uber-lyft-and-zimride-cheap-and-fun-ways-to-get-around-in-the-us/map_607vor9h/" title="map_607vor9h"><img data-liked="0" data-reblogged="0" data-attachment-id="12942" data-orig-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/map_607vor9h.png" data-orig-size="268,268" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta=''{"aperture":"0","credit":"","camera":"","caption":"","created_timestamp":"0","copyright":"","focal_length":"0","iso":"0","shutter_speed":"0","title":""}'' data-image-title="map_607vor9h" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/map_607vor9h.png?w=268" data-large-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/map_607vor9h.png?w=268" width="150" height="150" src="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/map_607vor9h.png?w=150&h=150" alt="The receipt gets sent with a map of the route, the average speed, time, etc."></a>\n\n<h2><a href="http://www.lyft.me/">Lyft</a></h2>\n<p>Lyft is the really cool service I discovered thanks to Nick in San Francisco. One thing I hate in SF is how expensive getting around can be, with two separate metro systems and varying metro fares depending on how far you go (unlike the simple 2.5USD fixed rate in New York’s MTA to anywhere in the system, buses included). Also, the BART system closes at 2:00AM, cutting your night short. You can find Lyfts well past that, so even more reason to love it.</p>\n<p>Lyft is basically a service that links people looking for a ride with folks that need one, but within a certain region (not cross-country trips). Drivers sign up and get a background check, and they get sent a huge pink, furry mustache they attach to the grills of their cars. Then, all you do is pinpoint your location and request a lyft. In minutes, the driver arrives and you hop in. Drivers are normal people and these are their private cars. Often, they’re young and hip and the conversations are very pleasant.</p>\n<p>Once you complete the trip, since this is not technically a taxi and cannot charge fares, Lyft suggests a “donation” amount based on the distance and time. You can of course be an asshole and donate a dollar only, but then, you’ll get blacklisted and no one would wanna pick you up. You can also rate the driver so that you let others know if he or she was bad or unpleasant. Luckily, the 5 times we used Lyft, all our drivers were really sweet and accommodating.</p>\n<p>This is epic and the fact it can function is a loophole I hope never gets closed. It’s also really good money on the side if you have a car and some free time. A perfect occasion to use Lyft would be on weekend nights, so you don’t drunk drive and get to go back and forth between the several happening parts of the city cheaply and in a fun way.</p>\n\n<a href="http://ginosblog.com/2013/04/09/uber-lyft-and-zimride-cheap-and-fun-ways-to-get-around-in-the-us/screenshot_2013-04-08-09-36-47/" title="Screenshot_2013-04-08-09-36-47"><img data-liked="0" data-reblogged="0" data-attachment-id="12949" data-orig-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-08-09-36-47.png" data-orig-size="720,1280" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta=''{"aperture":"0","credit":"","camera":"","caption":"","created_timestamp":"0","copyright":"","focal_length":"0","iso":"0","shutter_speed":"0","title":""}'' data-image-title="Screenshot_2013-04-08-09-36-47" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-08-09-36-47.png?w=168" data-large-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-08-09-36-47.png?w=576" width="84" height="150" src="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-08-09-36-47.png?w=84&h=150" alt="Request it and in seconds, you get shown your driver + car"></a>\n<a href="http://ginosblog.com/2013/04/09/uber-lyft-and-zimride-cheap-and-fun-ways-to-get-around-in-the-us/screenshot_2013-04-08-09-40-07/" title="Screenshot_2013-04-08-09-40-07"><img data-liked="0" data-reblogged="0" data-attachment-id="12950" data-orig-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-08-09-40-07.png" data-orig-size="720,1280" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta=''{"aperture":"0","credit":"","camera":"","caption":"","created_timestamp":"0","copyright":"","focal_length":"0","iso":"0","shutter_speed":"0","title":""}'' data-image-title="Screenshot_2013-04-08-09-40-07" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-08-09-40-07.png?w=168" data-large-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-08-09-40-07.png?w=576" width="84" height="150" src="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-08-09-40-07.png?w=84&h=150" alt="A notification that the driver is there"></a>\n<a href="http://ginosblog.com/2013/04/09/uber-lyft-and-zimride-cheap-and-fun-ways-to-get-around-in-the-us/628x471/" title="628x471"><img data-liked="0" data-reblogged="0" data-attachment-id="12952" data-orig-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/628x471.jpg" data-orig-size="628,469" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta=''{"aperture":"0","credit":"","camera":"","caption":"","created_timestamp":"0","copyright":"","focal_length":"0","iso":"0","shutter_speed":"0","title":""}'' data-image-title="628×471" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/628x471.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/628x471.jpg?w=610" width="150" height="112" src="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/628x471.jpg?w=150&h=112" alt="The pink mustache!"></a>\n<a href="http://ginosblog.com/2013/04/09/uber-lyft-and-zimride-cheap-and-fun-ways-to-get-around-in-the-us/screenshot_2013-04-08-09-40-27/" title="Screenshot_2013-04-08-09-40-27"><img data-liked="0" data-reblogged="0" data-attachment-id="12951" data-orig-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-08-09-40-27.png" data-orig-size="720,1280" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta=''{"aperture":"0","credit":"","camera":"","caption":"","created_timestamp":"0","copyright":"","focal_length":"0","iso":"0","shutter_speed":"0","title":""}'' data-image-title="Screenshot_2013-04-08-09-40-27" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-08-09-40-27.png?w=168" data-large-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-08-09-40-27.png?w=576" width="84" height="150" src="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screenshot_2013-04-08-09-40-27.png?w=84&h=150" alt="You''re on your way!"></a>\n\n<h2><a href="http://zimride.com/">Zimride</a></h2>\n<p>This is like Lyft but for longer distances and roadtrips. I went down from SF to LA for just 35$ with two very fun people in a very comfortable and scenic ride. Faster and cheaper than a train, more comfortable and faster than a bus and definitely cheaper than a flight. You punch in your route, check who’s offering seats, get in contact and if the driver OKs you, you call up each other, set a meeting point and then it’s roadtrip time!</p>\n<p>I loved this because it’s cheap, but more importantly, fun. You get to meet strangers and by the end of the trip become friends. Of course, I did have a wee bit hard time getting a driver which isn’t afraid of a fat, bearded Arab guy, but, after a few attempts, it did work out and I ended up with two new friends in LA.</p>\n\n<a href="http://ginosblog.com/2013/04/09/uber-lyft-and-zimride-cheap-and-fun-ways-to-get-around-in-the-us/screen-shot-2013-04-09-at-7-15-10-pm/" title="Screen shot 2013-04-09 at 7.15.10 PM"><img data-liked="0" data-reblogged="0" data-attachment-id="12953" data-orig-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screen-shot-2013-04-09-at-7-15-10-pm-e1365523471345.png" data-orig-size="1292,694" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta=''{"aperture":"0","credit":"","camera":"","caption":"","created_timestamp":"0","copyright":"","focal_length":"0","iso":"0","shutter_speed":"0","title":""}'' data-image-title="Screen shot 2013-04-09 at 7.15.10 PM" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screen-shot-2013-04-09-at-7-15-10-pm-e1365523471345.png?w=300" data-large-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screen-shot-2013-04-09-at-7-15-10-pm-e1365523471345.png?w=610" width="150" height="80" src="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screen-shot-2013-04-09-at-7-15-10-pm-e1365523471345.png?w=150&h=80" alt="Punch in coordinates"></a>\n<a href="http://ginosblog.com/2013/04/09/uber-lyft-and-zimride-cheap-and-fun-ways-to-get-around-in-the-us/screen-shot-2013-04-09-at-7-15-24-pm/" title="Screen shot 2013-04-09 at 7.15.24 PM"><img data-liked="0" data-reblogged="0" data-attachment-id="12954" data-orig-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screen-shot-2013-04-09-at-7-15-24-pm-e1365523532228.png" data-orig-size="985,714" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta=''{"aperture":"0","credit":"","camera":"","caption":"","created_timestamp":"0","copyright":"","focal_length":"0","iso":"0","shutter_speed":"0","title":""}'' data-image-title="Screen shot 2013-04-09 at 7.15.24 PM" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screen-shot-2013-04-09-at-7-15-24-pm-e1365523532228.png?w=300" data-large-file="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screen-shot-2013-04-09-at-7-15-24-pm-e1365523532228.png?w=610" width="150" height="108" src="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/screen-shot-2013-04-09-at-7-15-24-pm-e1365523532228.png?w=150&h=108" alt="Choose a driver, hope he/she accepts"></a>\n\n<br><a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/ginoraidy.wordpress.com/12941/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/ginoraidy.wordpress.com/12941/"></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=ginosblog.com&blog=11198665&post=12941&subd=ginoraidy&ref=&feed=1" width="1" height="1">'),
(1107, 'http://brofessionalreview.com/2013/04/09/our-kashida-secrets-02/', 'Our Kashida secrets 02', 'http://brofessionalreview.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/1.png?w=382&h=441', 'Our Kashida secrets 02\nBy Admin I: so the last kashida post ended with a reference from the khtt foundation, a series ...', 'brofessionalreview', 1365524160, '<p><a href="http://brofessionalreview.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/1.png"><img alt="1" src="http://brofessionalreview.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/1.png?w=382&h=441" width="382" height="441"></a></p>\n<p><strong>Our Kashida secrets 02</strong></p>\n<p><em><strong>By Admin I:</strong> </em>so<em> </em>the last kashida <a href="http://brofessionalreview.com/2013/04/02/our-kashida-secrets-01/">post</a> ended with a reference from the khtt foundation, a series of Kashida rules by Edo Smitshuijzen that were easily rebutted. The research continued, we decided for once to behave and stop making assumptions, so we stepped on some principles and contacted the so-called Arabic Type designers. Pascal Zoghbi is probably more famous than hipster eyeglasses when it comes to the Lebanese design community, known for Arabic branding adaptations, lettering and typeface design, Pascal is an academic, taught at many universities (LAU,NDU,AUB). So we’re stating all those bling-bling facts just to get to a point where his answer to our Kashida question came like:</p>\n<p>“there is no one source or proper kind of information about that, i tried once to write my own post about that, and was asking arabic calligraphers about the topic, and i did not get any proper or coherent logic for it. What i understood from the calligraphers is that some letters can have a madda after them, and others not.”</p>\n<p>Okay so, there’s nothing wrong with his ‘I don’t know’ other than the fact that he’s one of the most famous Arabic type designers that’s clearly too focused on the aesthetics of the language instead of searching for its rules and roots, or maybe a blunt decision of disregarding those rules. After his Lebanese-ish ‘i tried to do it first’ Pascal couldn’t give an answer. (He was probably too busy selling his ‘<a href="http://www.29arabicletters.com/foundry/?m=1-2-1&fid=37">Massira</a>‘ font, inspired by the Arab revolutions, by the mass, the street protestors, sold for $150 to $300 / kill me now).</p>\n<p><a href="http://brofessionalreview.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/6.png"><img alt="6" src="http://brofessionalreview.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/6.png?w=300&h=219" width="300" height="219"></a></p>\n<p>The quest didn’t stop, we tried to behave, like we reaaally tried, and contacted Nadine Chahine, yes the Linotype foundry Arabic fonts designer, the one responsible for many westernised typographical adaptations/cultural crimes.</p>\n<p><a href="http://brofessionalreview.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/3.png"><img alt="3" src="http://brofessionalreview.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/3.png?w=300&h=169" width="300" height="169"></a></p>\n<p>Nadine’s reply came ‘à la légère’ simply stating: “There are specific rules for where to apply the kashida and these are dependent on the number of letters in a word and the shape of letters (not the pronunciation). For example, the letter Sin is a good place to include a kashida as it already supports a long extension. Before the Alif is also another example”.</p>\n<p>Makes sense? has a purpose? a background? does it answer the ‘why’? No. no. Like no!</p>\n<p>So between Pascal and Nadine, things started feeling dizzy, disappointing, and big questions about the material taught in typography classes at universities started looking like a huge ball of paradoxical pretentious erroneous material. Free of culture/context.</p>\n<p>That was when we decided to consult a different sort of designers to be featured in our third post, but let me end this sequel with one sneak peek: “in fact, I would argue that people like Chahine and Zoghbi, in their Dubai-Mall approach to Latin/Arabic bastardization, are capitalistic but also Islamophobic in intent and purpose.” Says one of our next post’s contributors.</p>\n<p>Stay tuned for 03.</p>\n<br><a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/brofessionalreview.wordpress.com/2617/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/brofessionalreview.wordpress.com/2617/"></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=brofessionalreview.com&blog=28964988&post=2617&subd=brofessionalreview&ref=&feed=1" width="1" height="1">'),
(1108, 'http://ginosblog.com/2013/04/09/the-orange-house-project-and-saving-lebanons-giant-sea-turtles/', 'The Orange House Project and Saving Lebanon’s Giant Sea Turtles', 'http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/bpg-15.jpg?w=610&h=414', 'Look at those adorable new hatchlings making their way into the sea seconds after seeing the first light of day. Many of...', 'ginosblog', 1365525660, '<p>\n</p><p><a href="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/bpg-15.jpg"><img alt="bPG-15" src="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/bpg-15.jpg?w=610&h=414" width="610" height="414"></a></p>\n<p>\n</p><p>Look at those adorable new hatchlings making their way into the sea seconds after seeing the first light of day. Many of them will die because of the unforgiving environment they go into, and of course because of us. Some lucky ones do survive, and they return to the very shore they were born on in Tyre and lay their own eggs years later, generation after generation, for thousands of years.</p>\n<p>This isn’t a photo I took off a Planet Earth episode, this is from <a href="http://www.orangehouseproject.com/PhotoGallery.php">The Orange House Porject</a>‘s website taken on a Lebanese shore…</p>\n<blockquote><p>For millennia, sea turtles have swum ashore every summer to lay their eggs on beaches in what is now southern Lebanon. After incubation, the hatchlings race across the sand from their nests to the sea at night. A chance encounter with a sea turtle one night in 1999 inspired Mona Khalil to create the conservation project at Mansouri and Kolaila that is unique in Lebanon. Mona, then living in the Netherlands, had returned to Lebanon to visit her family’s beachfront farm. One moonless night, she was amazed to spy a green turtle laying eggs on the beach – and when she discovered that turtles were in danger of vanishing from Lebanon, she immediately knew what she would do when she came back to live there…</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.orangehouseproject.com/AboutUs.php"><em>Read the rest of the inspiring story here</em></a></p></blockquote>\n<p>Of course, Israel isn’t our greatest problem, it’s our own corrupt leaders who seem to be on the verge of OK-ing a port project that would eradicate this millennia-old nesting ground. So please, sign this <a href="http://www.causes.com/actions/1706089-protect-naqura-rocky-coast-a-coastal-sea-reserve">petition</a> and let’s hope some day our kids will be able to witness this beautiful natural phenomenon that I was lucky enough to witness in my scouting days.</p>\n<p><span><iframe type="text/html" width="610" height="374" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/ZuG3OJgHlWU?version=3&rel=1&fs=1&showsearch=0&showinfo=1&iv_load_policy=1&wmode=transparent" frameborder="0"></iframe></span></p>\n<br><a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/ginoraidy.wordpress.com/12958/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/ginoraidy.wordpress.com/12958/"></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=ginosblog.com&blog=11198665&post=12958&subd=ginoraidy&ref=&feed=1" width="1" height="1">'),
(1109, 'http://blogbaladi.com/the-zouk-mosbeh-bridge/', 'The Zouk Mosbeh bridge', 'http://img.youtube.com/vi/IhE51bT11mQ/0.jpg', '[YouTube]\nI have to pass by this bridge on a daily basis and feel my car is going to break everytime I run over this par...', 'blogbaladi', 1365531420, '<p><iframe width="420" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/IhE51bT11mQ" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe> [<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IhE51bT11mQ">YouTube</a>]</p>\n<p>I have to pass by this bridge on a daily basis and feel my car is going to break everytime I run over this part of the bridge. The other alternative is <a href="http://blogbaladi.com/marche-du-pont-bridge-no-longer-safe/">the Marche du Pont bridge</a> that’s also in bad shape.</p>'),
(1110, 'http://www.h20-platform.com/2013/04/another-fracture-in-googles-glasses.html', 'Another fracture in Google''s Glasses!', NULL, 'Sorry, but when you have your Google Glasses on, you will not be able to, to enter to a  local cinema or to your favori...', 'h20-platform', 1365531420, '<div dir="ltr" trbidi="on">\n<span lang="en"><span>Sorry, but</span> <span></span></span><span lang="en"><span><span lang="en"><span>when you</span> have your <span>Google</span> <span>Glasses</span> <span>on, you</span></span> will not be able </span><span>to</span>, to enter to a <span></span> <span>local cinema</span> <span>or to your</span> <span>favorite</span> <span>strip club</span>.</span><br><span lang="en"></span><br><br><div>\n<a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-sv408R64G7c/UWRZYx73RfI/AAAAAAAABFQ/sTiJYYHp8yA/s1600/bannedg.jpg" imageanchor="1"><img alt="Google glasses banned in strip clubs and cinemas" border="0" height="320" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-sv408R64G7c/UWRZYx73RfI/AAAAAAAABFQ/sTiJYYHp8yA/s320/bannedg.jpg" title="Google glasses banned " width="240"></a></div>\n<br><span>Already tested</span> <span>by some</span> <span>lucky</span> <span>picked users,</span> <span>the</span> <span>Google</span> <span>Glasses are</span><span></span> <span>not </span> <span>welcome</span> <span>in cinemas</span> <span>or in</span> <span>striptease</span> <span>clubs</span>. <span>A</span> <span>spokesman for the</span> <span>Sapphire</span> <span>Gentlemen''s</span> <span>Club</span> <span>in Las</span> <span>Vegas</span> <span>has</span> <span>made ​​it clear that</span> <span>due to the</span> <span>confidential nature of the</span> <span>activities taking place in</span> <span>his club</span> and <span></span>such <span>clubs</span> <span>in general,</span> and the hunt <span>for </span> <span>photos and videos</span> <span>leaked</span><span> by</span> <span>smartphones for many years, </span><span></span> <span>Google Glasses will be banned</span>.<br><span lang="en"> <span> </span></span><br><span lang="en"><span>And in case </span><span>customers refuse to</span> take off<span> their</span> <span>glasses,</span> <span>"They will be</span> <span>escorted</span> <span>to their hotel</span> <span>in a limousine</span>," <span>he adds.</span><br><br><span>And concerning the ban from cinemas, I don''t think that it needs much explanation. It is only rational, no? </span><br><br><span>But</span><a href="http://www.h20-platform.com/2013/03/would-you-give-up-your-private-life-for.html"> <span>Google</span> <span>Glasses</span> <span>could lead</span> <span>to</span> <span>other security issues</span>,<span> privacy related issues</span></a>. <span>Not to mention the abusive</span> <span>use that may</span> <span>be made by</span> <span>sexual predators.</span> <span>Moreover</span>, in this regard, Drew <span>Donofrio</span>, a private detective <span>working</span> <span>since 12 years for</span> <span>the</span> <span>Bergen</span> <span>County,</span> <span>confessed</span> <span>to worry about</span> <span>this problem on</span> <span>NBC</span> <span>News.</span></span><br><span lang="en"></span><br><span lang="en"><span><br></span></span>\n<span lang="en"><span>Source: NBC news.</span></span></div>\n<div>\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/gGBiZ?a=RMFVKZiR_io:DPFcAXZ7YjM:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/gGBiZ?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/gGBiZ?a=RMFVKZiR_io:DPFcAXZ7YjM:63t7Ie-LG7Y"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/gGBiZ?d=63t7Ie-LG7Y" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/gGBiZ?a=RMFVKZiR_io:DPFcAXZ7YjM:dnMXMwOfBR0"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/gGBiZ?d=dnMXMwOfBR0" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/gGBiZ?a=RMFVKZiR_io:DPFcAXZ7YjM:F7zBnMyn0Lo"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/gGBiZ?i=RMFVKZiR_io:DPFcAXZ7YjM:F7zBnMyn0Lo" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/gGBiZ?a=RMFVKZiR_io:DPFcAXZ7YjM:7Q72WNTAKBA"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/gGBiZ?d=7Q72WNTAKBA" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/gGBiZ?a=RMFVKZiR_io:DPFcAXZ7YjM:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/gGBiZ?i=RMFVKZiR_io:DPFcAXZ7YjM:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/gGBiZ?a=RMFVKZiR_io:DPFcAXZ7YjM:qj6IDK7rITs"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/gGBiZ?d=qj6IDK7rITs" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/gGBiZ?a=RMFVKZiR_io:DPFcAXZ7YjM:KwTdNBX3Jqk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/gGBiZ?i=RMFVKZiR_io:DPFcAXZ7YjM:KwTdNBX3Jqk" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/gGBiZ?a=RMFVKZiR_io:DPFcAXZ7YjM:l6gmwiTKsz0"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/gGBiZ?d=l6gmwiTKsz0" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/gGBiZ?a=RMFVKZiR_io:DPFcAXZ7YjM:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/gGBiZ?i=RMFVKZiR_io:DPFcAXZ7YjM:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/gGBiZ?a=RMFVKZiR_io:DPFcAXZ7YjM:TzevzKxY174"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/blogspot/gGBiZ?d=TzevzKxY174" border="0"></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/blogspot/gGBiZ/~4/RMFVKZiR_io" height="1" width="1">'),
(1111, 'http://www.larmoiredelana.com/?p=10767', 'Style your closet: With Vertical Stripes', 'http://www.larmoiredelana.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/zara2-1024x791.jpg', 'Clothing patterns affect visual perception. Based on this, I want to tackle a recent Spring 2013 trend (vertical stripes...', 'larmoiredelana', 1365531600, '<p><span>Clothing patterns affect visual perception. Based on this, I want to tackle a recent Spring 2013 trend (vertical stripes) and give you few tips on how to rock it according to your body structure.</span><br><span> Take a look at any style blog or fashion magazine and you will see stripes in every color and variety of widths.</span><br><span> YES, vertical stripes have a slimming effect, don’t you love this trend already!? On dresses, tops, shoes or event skirts, stripes are fun to style. Moreover, they say that wearing vertical stripes makes you seem taller but if you’re petite, it’s important to remember that the thinner the stripes, the better.</span><br><span> Most SS13 collections had a touch of vertical stripes, especially the black&white ones, which are definitely the most flattering ones! </span><br><span> Few tips on how to wear vertical stripes:</span><br><span><strong> 1. LONG AND LEAN: </strong>Pants or skirts with vertical stripes are a very flattering look, especially paired with a solid colored blouse or T-shirt.<br><a href="http://www.larmoiredelana.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/zara2.jpg" rel="lightbox[10767]"><span><img title="zara2" src="http://www.larmoiredelana.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/zara2-1024x791.jpg" alt="zara2 1024x791 Style your closet: With Vertical Stripes" width="584" height="451"></span></a> <strong>2. CLASSICAL OR SEASONAL:</strong> The great thing with vertical stripes is that you can go from traditional blue-and-white, black-and-white or red-and-white color palette, or look for crazier options: pink, yellow, bright green and baby blue would look so fresh and different.<br><a href="http://www.larmoiredelana.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/verticalstripes1.jpg" rel="lightbox[10767]"><span><img title="verticalstripes1" src="http://www.larmoiredelana.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/verticalstripes1-1024x791.jpg" alt="verticalstripes1 1024x791 Style your closet: With Vertical Stripes" width="584" height="451"></span></a> <strong>3. FIND THE PERFECT STRIPED T-SHIRT:</strong> Every woman needs a classic navy and white striped boat-neck three-quarter length sleeves t-shirt. First popularized by Coco Chanel, it would look perfect with an A-line skirt, slim red cropped pants, ballet flats or even on a pair of navy blue jeans/shorts with a pair of white converse. </span><br><span><strong> 4. COLOR-BLOCKED STRIPES:</strong> one of the hottest stripes trend this spring is to wear two/three or even more colored stripes. Examples: a top with black & white stripes in front and pink & white stripes on the back.<br><a href="http://www.larmoiredelana.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/zara3.jpg" rel="lightbox[10767]"><span><img title="zara3" src="http://www.larmoiredelana.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/zara3-1024x791.jpg" alt="zara3 1024x791 Style your closet: With Vertical Stripes" width="584" height="451"></span></a> <strong>5: ACCESSORIZE WITH STRIPES:</strong> Add a graphic punch to your outfit by choosing accessories with multi-colored stripes. A scarf, handbag, headband or a pair of shoes will be perfect ways of sporting the trend especially if you’re not fan of stripes on clothing items. A huge tote with black&white stripes would be so nice to style with comfy and colorful summer outfits. I’d personally even go onto trying a striped manicure or pedicure, this could be so much fun!</span><br><span> Time to add a little punch to your wardrobe this spring!<br>\nPicture courtesy: www.zara.com </span><br><span> Fashionably yours,</span><br><span> Lana xx </span></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.facebook.com/share.php?u=http://www.larmoiredelana.com/?p=10767" target="_blank" title="Share on Facebook">Share on Facebook</a></p>'),
(1112, 'http://www.beirutreport.com/2013/04/a-request-for-information.html', 'A request for information', 'http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-vUo9PNDxqew/UWRbuS54KzI/AAAAAAAAEtM/kP78wzFPYek/s640/Screen+Shot+2013-04-09+at+9.15.02+PM.png', 'Dear Mr. Hariri, The internet has been totally pathetic lately, half as pathetic as usual that is.Though I and thousand...', 'beirutreport', 1365532860, '<div dir="ltr" trbidi="on"><div><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-Jb4y0Q_euio/UWRfiyaNYUI/AAAAAAAAEtY/HJDeo9ZHMNE/s1600/Unknown-1.jpeg" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="342" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-Jb4y0Q_euio/UWRfiyaNYUI/AAAAAAAAEtY/HJDeo9ZHMNE/s400/Unknown-1.jpeg" width="400"></a></div><div><br></div><div>Dear Mr. Hariri, </div><div><br></div><div>The internet has been totally pathetic lately, half as pathetic as usual that is.</div><div><br></div><div>Though I and thousands of other Lebanese are <a href="http://www.beirutreport.com/2013/04/the-additional-gig-money-trap.html" target="_blank">paying an arm and a leg for glacial speeds</a> like 1mbps, what we are getting this week is actually half of that:</div><div><br></div><div><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-vUo9PNDxqew/UWRbuS54KzI/AAAAAAAAEtM/kP78wzFPYek/s1600/Screen+Shot+2013-04-09+at+9.15.02+PM.png" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="102" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-vUo9PNDxqew/UWRbuS54KzI/AAAAAAAAEtM/kP78wzFPYek/s640/Screen+Shot+2013-04-09+at+9.15.02+PM.png" width="640"></a></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>The telecom minister is blaming your man at Ogero, Abdel Moneim Youssef and he''s just purchased Facebook ads to publicize that:</div><div><br></div><div>                          <a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-SdNaNwMfWl8/UWRbuUth3UI/AAAAAAAAEtI/9eLzVIYMspM/s1600/Screen+Shot+2013-04-09+at+5.03.21+PM.png" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="191" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-SdNaNwMfWl8/UWRbuUth3UI/AAAAAAAAEtI/9eLzVIYMspM/s400/Screen+Shot+2013-04-09+at+5.03.21+PM.png" width="400"></a></div><div><br></div><div>The ads are linked to his Facebook status where Minister Sehnaoui explains that Youssef is not releasing bandwidth to ISPs, thus "strangling" bandwidth to the whole country:</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><a href="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-Q7qfdl4ecT4/UWRbto3U7tI/AAAAAAAAEtA/5ESPpro5IOU/s1600/Screen+Shot+2013-04-09+at+5.05.54+PM.png" imageanchor="1"><img border="0" height="152" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-Q7qfdl4ecT4/UWRbto3U7tI/AAAAAAAAEtA/5ESPpro5IOU/s640/Screen+Shot+2013-04-09+at+5.05.54+PM.png" width="640"></a></div><div><br></div><br><div>Youssef won''t speak to the media; <a href="http://www.beirutreport.com/2012/08/the-elusive-mr-youssef.html" target="_blank">he won''t even answer the phone</a> when MPs in your political party try to call him, as I found out. </div><div><br></div><div>Even an <a href="http://www.beirutreport.com/2013/04/frank-talk-with-ogero-technician.html" target="_blank">Ogero employee has told me</a> Youssef is obstructing the internet in Lebanon.</div><div><br></div><div>Mr. Hariri, I think the citizens of Lebanon deserve an explanation. Are you supporting this man and is he slowing down our internet? </div><div><br></div><div>Thanks. </div><br></div>'),
(1113, 'http://www.tasteofbeirut.com/2013/04/dried-lime-tea-chai-noomi-basra/', 'Dried lime tea (Chai noomi Basra)', 'http://tasteofbeirut.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Tea-with-dried-limes.jpg', 'This infusion is popular in Iraq; it is made by seeding the noomi Basra or dried limes and simmering the peels in water ...', 'tasteofbeirut', 1365536100, '<p><a href="http://tasteofbeirut.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Tea-with-dried-limes.jpg"><img alt="Tea with dried limes" src="http://tasteofbeirut.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Tea-with-dried-limes.jpg" width="650" height="434"></a></p>\n<p><span><strong>This infusion is popular in Iraq; it is made by seeding the noomi Basra or dried limes and simmering the peels in water for 15 to 30 minutes; drain and sweeten. Apparently it helps with tummy aches and digestive issues. </strong></span></p>\n<p><strong>I did not have the patience of seeding the limes, I simply poked each in 3 places, dumped them in lots of water and simmered them for 15 minutes. I used 2 limes for a quart of water. I added sugar (or honey) to the infusion as it tends to taste sour. </strong></p>'),
(1114, 'http://ginosblog.com/2013/04/09/forgive-them-father-for-they-know-not-what-google-is-and-trust-facebook-blindly/', 'Forgive Them Father, For They Know Not What Google Is and Trust Facebook Blindly', 'http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/72598_626264194055378_497823605_n.jpg?w=610', '1- It never got into Lebanon\n\nSource\nSo, I’m not sure why you’re demanding “all authorities in Lebanon” and the ...', 'ginosblog', 1365537660, '<h2>1- It never got into Lebanon</h2>\n<p><a href="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/72598_626264194055378_497823605_n.jpg"><img alt="72598_626264194055378_497823605_n" src="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/72598_626264194055378_497823605_n.jpg?w=610"></a></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=626264194055378&set=a.519960778019054.134938.488797521135380&type=1&theater&refsrc=http%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FNKj1S3PYDF">Source</a></p>\n<p>So, I’m not sure why you’re demanding “all authorities in Lebanon” and the government to intervene when that specific design never actually got into Lebanon, but featured on Bershka’s website only. Here, I also wanna tell Bershka, bravo for caving into pressure from clueless conservatives instead of standing by your brand and you know, logic and reality since <em>nothing</em> was offensive except the reaction by some Lebanese to another country’s religious symbol.</p>\n<h2>2- It’s Santa Muerte, a sacred icon for millions of Christians</h2>\n<p><a href="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/220px-santa-muerte-nlaredo2.jpg"><img alt="220px-Santa-muerte-nlaredo2" src="http://ginoraidy.files.wordpress.com/2013/04/220px-santa-muerte-nlaredo2.jpg?w=610"></a>In Lebanon, channels like MTV and Al Jadeed are famous for not knowing about the invention we call “Google”. They think the Monster Energy Drink logo is a “satanic symbol”, so you can’t really blame them for completely missing the point here. The “satanism” sensationalism that swept Lebanon a few years back, still lingers, and people are afraid when they see skulls or kids with long hair and a Metallica t-shirt. This though, was simply ignorant and 0.02 seconds on Google could’ve resolved that issue.</p>\n<blockquote><p>Santa Muerte generally appears as a female skeletal figure, clad in a long robe and holding one or more objects, usually a <a title="Scythe" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scythe">scythe</a>and a <a title="Globe" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Globe">globe</a>.<sup><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Santa_Muerte#cite_note-5">[5]</a></sup> Her robe can be of any color, as more specific images of the figure vary widely from devotee to devotee and according to the rite being performed or the petition being made.<sup><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Santa_Muerte#cite_note-oriana1318-6">[6]</a></sup> As the worship of Santa Muerte was clandestine until the 20th century, most prayers and other rites have been traditionally performed privately in the home. However, for the past ten years or so, worship has become more public, especially in <a title="Mexico City" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico_City">Mexico City</a> after Enriqueta Romero initiated her famous Mexico City shrine in 2001.<sup><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Santa_Muerte#cite_note-Garma-4">[4]</a></sup><sup><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Santa_Muerte#cite_note-Villarreal-7">[7]</a></sup><sup><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Santa_Muerte#cite_note-Chesnut-8">[8]</a></sup> The number of believers in Santa Muerte has grown over the past ten to twenty years, to several million followers in Mexico, the United States, and parts of Central America. Santa Muerte has similar male counterparts in the Americas, such as the skeletal folk saints <a title="San La Muerte" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_La_Muerte">San La Muerte</a> of Argentina and Rey (King) Pascual of Guatemala.<sup><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Santa_Muerte#cite_note-Chesnut-8">[8]</a></sup></p>\n<p><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Santa_Muerte">source: Wikipedia</a></p></blockquote>\n<p>The sad part was, that when the bigots were made aware of this bit of information, instead of admitting their misinformed mistake, they poked fun at people for actually knowing or caring to look up Santa Muerte. As for Santa Muerte being looked down upon by the Catholic Church, so are condoms and contraceptives, but I’m sure most of you look past that, no?</p>\n<p>So, being offended and organizing a Crusade against this is both un-Christian and also incredibly humiliating to the Christian faith. It’s also racist and elitist since we went down that way.</p>\n<h2>3- Freedom of Speech and Expression</h2>\n<p>Religion is like any other topic. If it’s sacred to you, it’s sacred to you. No need to force other people to have the same respect and reverence to whatever your worship. You can criticize and disagree, but calling for it’s ban and government intervention, is backwards and more fitting for countries like Iran or Saudi, so please move there.</p>\n<h2>4- Christian Values?</h2>\n<p>I was raised a Christian all my life. All I was taught is love, forgiveness, tolerance, not to persecute others, to be meek, to be kind, that pride was the cardinal sin, etc. Yet, I see all the people jumping up and down proclaiming to be the standard bearers of the Christian faith, doing the complete opposite of what Jesus said. Seriously, if Jesus came back right now, I’d hate to see how awkward everyone complaining about the tshirt would be in his presence.</p>\n<p>As for the example of Jesus getting mad in the Temple (which all machoman Christians adore), he got mad because people were using religion to make money, which is every single clergy member today. He didn’t tell his followers “attack everyone who insults me now!” he said “turn the other cheek” and “wipe the dust off your sandals and move on” and got lashed and humiliated and crucified, instead of leading a rebellion on the authorities.</p>\n<h2>5- Stubbornness beyond the reasonable</h2>\n<p>Yet, despite everything, some people <em>still</em> insist this is something they need to fight, despite its nonexistence and their failed grasp of the situation. Personally, I think this is utterly humiliating to the Christian faith, which often prides itself on being the more progressive one in the region where chopping heads off and burning the wrong embassy over cartoons is still a thing in 2013.</p>\n<h2>In Conclusion</h2>\n<p>HAHAHAHAHAHAHAHA! Thank you for the laughs everyone! As if the fact this wasn’t even being sold here was embarrassing enough, you went on to show the intolerant, racist sides of you that even in the face of insurmountable evidence, stick to the hatred and bigotry that is supposed to be the very opposite of what your faith promotes.</p>\n<p>And for all the devout Christians out there, remember what St. Augustine said “It was pride that changed angels into devils; it is humility that makes men as angels.” (that’s if you want to be good Christians, and not sectarian Lebanese)</p>\n<br><a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/ginoraidy.wordpress.com/12962/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/ginoraidy.wordpress.com/12962/"></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=ginosblog.com&blog=11198665&post=12962&subd=ginoraidy&ref=&feed=1" width="1" height="1">');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`post_id`, `post_url`, `post_title`, `post_image`, `post_excerpt`, `blog_id`, `post_timestamp`, `post_content`) VALUES
(1115, 'http://www.toomextra.com/2013/04/le-liban-reve-dun-occidental-ou-le.html', 'Le Liban rêvé d’un occidental : ou le pouvoir de la littérature', NULL, ' Le Liban rêvé d’un occidental : ou le pouvoir de la littératureDepuis  que j’ai mis les pieds pour la première...', 'toomextra', 1365538320, '<div dir="ltr" trbidi="on"><br><div><div> Le Liban rêvé d’un occidental : ou le pouvoir de la littérature<br><br></div><span>Depuis  que j’ai mis les pieds pour la première fois au Liban, moi petit  européen ignorant de l’Orient, je me suis pris d’une passion soudaine  pour ce qu’on écrit sur ce pays, ou sur les romans qu’on y situe, et je  ne sais pas pourquoi, le Liban que j’ai découvert dans les livres m’a  touché, et me fait dire que ce pays est, pour paraphraser ses habitants «  le plus beau pays du monde », en connaissant bien entendu la sciences  légendaire de l’exagération des libanais.</span><br><br><span>De  grands auteurs ont écrit sur le Liban : Lamartine, Nerval et  Chateaubriand pour ne citer qu’eux, l’on aimé et y ont séjourné avec  plaisir, lui donnant une certaine image d’Epinal certes, mais qui n’est  pas dénuée de vérité. D’ailleurs les livres ne sont jamais dénués de  vérité : les trois écrivains précités parlent de l’argent qu’ils ont  laissé… Mais ces grands romantiques ont commencé à construire mon  imaginaire libanais, au-delà des conflits et des problèmes de la vie  quotidienne, et à part ma femme, c’est sans doute les trois personnes  qui m’ont fait aimer le Liban, jusqu’à présent. Mais les français n’ont  pas l’apanage de la glorification du Pays du Cèdre, d’ailleurs qui  d’autre pourrait mieux le faire que ces habitant eux-mêmes ! Alexandre  Najjar, Amine Maalouf, Venus Khoury-Ghata, Nadia Tuèni m’ont tous permis  de joindre le rêve à la réalité : tous parlent des conflits, de ce qui  s’y est passé, mais ils ont su aller plus loin en y plaçant des  histoires, en y créant des personnages issus de leurs réalités, de leur  intimité avec leur Terre, et c’est là ce qui fait aimer le Liban. Pour  un occidental, le Liban est un pays en guerre permanente (excusez moi le  stéréotype, mais nos journaux vous présentent comme cela, même si je  connais la réalité, maintenant), mais le fait de lire des écrivains  aimant leur pays, et le faisant aller au-delà de la guerre, le  transcende ; et m’ont permis d’avoir envie de le découvrir et de l’aimer  ; et désolé pour la bouffe, les chicha-deliveries et les Roof Tops,  mais Alexandre Najjar m’a rendu le pays plus aimable que vous (sans  offense pour toutes les charmantes « tantes » que je connais là-bas).</span></div><div><br>Au delà des écrivains académiques, de simple bloggeurs publiant  des livres, comme Toom Extra, ou Nasri Attallah, ou comme le nombre de «  You know what… » ou de récits tous plus ou moins littéraires publiés  sur le et au Liban sont des choses merveilleuses, des textes qui  présentent un autre Liban, un Liban personnel, différent de la grande  Histoire. Des récits de vie comme celui de Darina Al-Joundi, qui font  que, malgré le tragique, on aime ce pays pour les personnages fictifs  qu’on sait exister dans quelques recoins de ce pays. Bref, comment un  pays qui peut produire autant de littérature, d’histoire et d’imaginaire  autour de lui ne peut il pas être aimable ? Le Suisse n’a que peu de  vrais écrivains qui écrivent sur elle (et qui se doivent de la  détester), mais le Liban en foisonne !</div><div><br></div><div>Merci donc à tous ces auteurs de m’avoir fait aimer le Liban, même si cela paraît fleur bleue, n’oubliez pas ce que j’ai dit au début : « Les livres ne sont jamais dénués de vérité... »<br><div><span><br></span></div></div></div>'),
(1116, 'http://www.thedscoop.com/post/47564060956', 'Beirut Women''s Marathon- May 26', 'http://media.tumblr.com/d087d6cea5a503a14a2ce04927f3cd6d/tumblr_inline_ml0ajcJCbl1qz4rgp.png', 'LADIES, it’s time to run/walk the Beirut Women’s Marathon! Get yourselves ready for Sunday May 26, 2013 to highl...', 'thedscoop', 1365542100, '<p><img src="http://media.tumblr.com/d087d6cea5a503a14a2ce04927f3cd6d/tumblr_inline_ml0ajcJCbl1qz4rgp.png"></p>\n\n<p><strong>LADIES</strong>, it’s time to run/walk the <strong>Beirut Women’s Marathon</strong>! Get yourselves ready for <strong>Sunday May 26</strong>, <strong>2013</strong> to highlight issues for women empowerment such as women in decision making roles, gender equality, violence against women, women’s right to grant her citizenship to her children, women in the parliament, etc. The Beirut Marathon Association, chaired by Mrs. May el Khalil, with the participation of The National Commission for Lebanese Women (NCLW), will be organizing the event.</p>\n<p><span>The registration fee is only <strong>$20</strong>. You can participate in either a 5K walk or a 10K run. While we the women run, our male counterparts (husbands, fiancés, boyfriends, friends who are boys) will be standing to cheer for us!</span></p>\n<p><span>For info and registration, visit <a href="http://www.beirutmarathon.org/">www.beirutmarathon.org</a>, Virgin Megastores, or contact Bassel (70/071107)</span></p>\n<p><span><img src="http://media.tumblr.com/d2be5aa4abb0a8195795d0ad01ec4165/tumblr_inline_ml0avnyKnb1qz4rgp.jpg"></span></p>'),
(1117, 'http://www.plus961.com/2013/04/new-virus-targeting-lebanese-internet-users/', 'New virus targeting Lebanese internet users', 'http://img.youtube.com/vi/ahKQffRwr38/0.jpg', 'Apparently there’s some new virus targeting Lebanese porn surfers that displays a fake warning once you visit some x-r...', 'plus961', 1365542040, '<p>Apparently there’s some new virus targeting Lebanese porn surfers that displays a fake warning once you visit some x-rated website, claiming you have violated the law and requires that you pay a fine of 200,000 L.L to the ministry of interior via <a href="http://www.cashu.com/" target="_blank">cashU</a> or face 8 months to 1 year in prison.</p>\n<p></p><center><iframe src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/ahKQffRwr38" height="338" width="450" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0"></iframe></center>So if you ever get that fake message, just keep calm and carry on browsing! (But consider maybe updating your antivirus once you’re done).\n<p>On a side note, the reporter needs to take a chill pill towards porn websites.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Plus961/~4/dSg7N50P-yM" height="1" width="1">'),
(1118, 'http://eyeontheeast.org/2013/04/10/shukran-qatar/', 'Shukran Qatar', NULL, 'Apparently, the world has had much to thank Qatar for in recent years. And if you haven’t been thanking it, check your...', 'eyeontheeast', 1365547080, 'Apparently, the world has had much to thank Qatar for in recent years. And if you haven’t been thanking it, check your closest government office, local opposition force or ailing business conglomerate for details. One of them is sure to … <a href="http://eyeontheeast.org/2013/04/10/shukran-qatar/">Continue reading <span>→</span></a><img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=eyeontheeast.org&blog=22913148&post=665&subd=eyeontheeast&ref=&feed=1" width="1" height="1">'),
(1119, 'http://www.plus961.com/2013/04/vox-cinemas-opening-today/', 'Vox Cinemas opening today', 'http://www.plus961.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/vox-cinemas-lebanon-300x200.jpg', 'According to Vox Cinemas’ page on Facebook, they’ll be opening today at Beirut City Centre.\n\nFor the list of movie t...', 'plus961', 1365552060, '<p>According to <a href="http://www.facebook.com/VOXCinemasLebanon">Vox Cinemas’ page</a> on Facebook, they’ll be opening today at <a title="Beirut City Centre opening" href="http://www.plus961.com/2013/04/beirut-city-centre-opening/">Beirut City Centre</a>.</p>\n<p><img alt="vox cinemas lebanon" src="http://www.plus961.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/vox-cinemas-lebanon-300x200.jpg" width="300" height="200"></p>\n<p>For the list of movie they’ll be showing, you can check their <a href="http://lbn.voxcinemas.com/">website</a>.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Plus961/~4/Wnh9A4zgseo" height="1" width="1">'),
(1120, 'http://blogbaladi.com/cnn-arabic-lebanese-mp-strida-geagea-among-the-sexiest-female-politicians-in-the-world/', 'CNN (Arabic): Lebanese MP Strida Geagea Among the Sexiest Female Politicians in the World', 'http://blogbaladi.com/images/setrida-geageamain1-425x221.jpg', 'The list included also Canadian Ruby Dhalla, Italian Maria Rosaria Carfagna and Sarah Palin. Check it out [Here].', 'blogbaladi', 1365556020, '<p><img src="http://blogbaladi.com/images/setrida-geageamain1-425x221.jpg" alt="setrida-geageamain1" width="425" height="221"></p>\n<p>The list included also Canadian Ruby Dhalla, Italian Maria Rosaria Carfagna and Sarah Palin. Check it out [<a href="http://arabic.cnn.com/2013/entertainment/4/9/world.sexiest.women/index.html">Here</a>].</p>'),
(1121, 'http://blogbaladi.com/cashu-virus-targeting-lebanese-porn-surfers/', 'CashU Virus targeting Lebanese porn surfers', 'http://blogbaladi.com/images/virus-425x267.jpg', 'Picture from Naharnet\nYou can read more about it and how to remove this virus [Here].\nInternal Security Forces cybercrim...', 'blogbaladi', 1365573480, '<p><img src="http://blogbaladi.com/images/virus-425x267.jpg" alt="virus" width="425" height="267"><br><em>Picture from <a href="http://www.naharnet.com/stories/en/78507-isf-warns-of-metropolitan-police-virus-hitting-computers-across-region">Naharnet</a></em></p>\n<p>You can read more about it and how to remove this virus [<a href="http://www.pcthreat.com/parasitebyid-30122en.html">Here</a>].</p>\n<blockquote><p>Internal Security Forces cybercrime and intellectual property unit warned on Saturday from a virus affecting mobile phones and computers, which has been spreading across the Middle East region and Lebanon lately.</p>\n<p>Hackers use the “Metropolitan Police Virus” to obtain the credit card’s balance when users enter their personal Cash U code.</p>\n<p>According to a statement issued by the ISF, the hackers can disable the Windows for users after displaying a bogus alert that says: “The ISF blocked your computer for violating copyright content on the web and you are obliged to pay a $200 fine.”</p>\n<p>The virus locks the computer and its applications, “whenever you try to log on into your Windows operating system or Safe Mode with Networking, it will display instead a lock screen asking you to pay a non-existing fine of $200 in the form of a CashU code.”</p>\n<p>The statement pointed out that the virus hits computers when a porn website is accessed or when an unknown program is downloaded.</p>\n<p>“Citizens have to pay attention and refrain from paying any amount of money using credit cards… They are also asked to inform the bureau of any hacking attempt,” it added.\n</p></blockquote>\n<p>Here’s a report done by Al-Jadeed on this matter. They never miss a chance to add drama to a story, even when it’s about porn.</p>\n<p><iframe width="420" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/ahKQffRwr38" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe><br><em>via +961</em> </p>\n<p>According to <a href="http://www.alexa.com/topsites/countries;2/LB">Alexa</a>, here are some of the most popular porn sites in Lebanon:</p>\n<p><img src="http://blogbaladi.com/images/p2-425x175.png" alt="p2" width="425" height="175"></p>\n<p><img src="http://blogbaladi.com/images/p1-425x264.png" alt="p1" width="425" height="264"></p>\n<p><img src="http://blogbaladi.com/images/p3-425x106.png" alt="p3" width="425" height="106"></p>'),
